---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const curatorName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_CURATOR_NAME || 'the curator';
const curatorHandle = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_CURATOR_HANDLE || '';
---

<Base title="About" description="About this oncology meeting digest.">
  <h2 style="margin-top:0">About this digest</h2>

  <p>
    This site publishes daily curated digests of the most impactful posts
    from oncology conferences on X (Twitter). It is a personal project,
    not affiliated with any conference or institution.
  </p>

  <h3>How it works</h3>
  <p>
    {curatorName} bookmarks the most clinically important tweets from each
    conference day. An AI pipeline groups them by topic, summarizes the
    discussion, and links to original sources. The site updates one or two
    times per conference day during major meetings.
  </p>

  <h3>What you get</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Curated by a human.</strong> Algorithmic feeds are noisy;
      a domain expert's bookmarks are the signal.</li>
    <li><strong>AI-summarized.</strong> Clusters of tweets become 1-2
      paragraph summaries with daily TL;DRs.</li>
    <li><strong>Citation-aware.</strong> NCT trial numbers, PubMed IDs,
      and DOIs auto-link to source records.</li>
    <li><strong>Links back to originals.</strong> The summary is a
      starting point. The original tweets are the source of truth.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What this is not</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Not medical advice.</strong> AI summaries can paraphrase
    incorrectly. Always verify against primary sources (clinicaltrials.gov,
    PubMed, the conference proceedings) before clinical use.
    <br /><br />
    <strong>Not exhaustive.</strong> This is one curator's filter. Many
    important findings will not appear here.
    <br /><br />
    <strong>Not affiliated</strong> with ASCO, ESMO, ASTRO, AACR, or any
    other organization.
  </p>

  <h3>Takedown requests</h3>
  <p>
    If you posted a tweet referenced here and would like it removed,
    contact {curatorHandle ? <a href={`https://x.com/${curatorHandle.replace(/^@/, '')}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{curatorHandle}</a> : 'the curator'} directly.
    Takedowns are typically actioned within 24 hours.
  </p>

  <h3>Source</h3>
  <p>
    This site is open source. Code at <a href="#">github</a> (link TBD).
  </p>
</Base>
